---
import InnerLayout from '../../layouts/InnerLayout.astro';

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebPage",
  "name": "AI HR Interviews — Exit Interviews, 360s & Employee Listening",
  "url": "https://anyinterview.to/for/hr-people",
  "description": "Run structured exit interviews, 360 feedback sessions, and employee listening at any scale. AnyInterview gives HR teams consistent data where before they had scattered notes.",
  "breadcrumb": {"@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"name":"Home","item":"https://anyinterview.to"},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"name":"HR & People","item":"https://anyinterview.to/for/hr-people"}]},
  "about": {"@type":"Service","name":"AI HR Interviews","provider":{"@type":"Organization","name":"AnyInterview","url":"https://anyinterview.to"},"serviceType":"AI-powered HR exit interviews and employee listening"}
};
---
<InnerLayout
  title="AI HR Interviews — Exit Interviews, 360s & Employee Listening | AnyInterview"
  description="Run structured exit interviews, 360 feedback, and employee listening at any scale. AnyInterview gives HR teams consistent data where before they had scattered notes."
  schema={schema}
  canonical="https://anyinterview.to/for/hr-people"
>

  <section class="ip-hero">
    <div class="ip-hero-inner">
      <p class="ip-eyebrow">HR &amp; People</p>
      <h1>Exit interviews that <em>people actually complete.</em></h1>
      <p class="ip-hero-sub">Most exit interviews never happen — or they're a checkbox nobody takes seriously. AnyInterview conducts structured HR interviews that feel like real conversations, not surveys. The data that should be driving your retention strategy, finally collected.</p>
      <div class="ip-cta-row">
        <a href="#" class="ip-cta-primary" data-action="open-demo">Book a Demo →</a>
        <a href="/security" class="ip-cta-secondary">Data privacy &amp; security</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="ip-section">
    <div class="ip-section-inner">
      <p class="ip-section-label">The Problem</p>
      <h2>The most honest feedback <em>you never collected.</em></h2>
      <p class="ip-section-lead">Departing employees know things your staying employees won't say. Most organizations collect none of it — or collect it in a rushed 10-minute call that's barely a formality.</p>
      <div class="hr-cols">
        <p>Exit interviews have a scheduling problem and a quality problem. The scheduling problem: HR teams are stretched, departing employees are checking out, and the interview gets deprioritized until the person is already gone. The quality problem: even when the interview happens, it's conducted by someone the employee may not want to be candid with.</p>
        <p>AnyInterview solves both. Departing employees can complete the interview on their own time, in their own words, without a manager in the room. The structure ensures every important question gets asked. The AI follow-ups probe for specifics when answers are vague. The result is a qualitatively richer data set than most HR teams have ever seen.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="ip-section--alt">
    <div class="ip-section-inner">
      <p class="ip-section-label">Programs We Power</p>
      <h2>HR conversations at <em>any scale.</em></h2>
      <p class="ip-section-lead">From exit interviews to skip-levels, every HR conversation that deserves a complete record — and rarely gets one.</p>
      <div class="ip-card-grid--4">
        <div class="ip-card">
          <div class="ip-card-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 00-4-4H5a4 4 0 00-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 00-3-3.87"/><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 010 7.75"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Exit interviews at scale</h3>
          <p>Every departing employee, not just the ones who happened to be leaving during a week when HR had time. Async, structured, complete.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ip-card">
          <div class="ip-card-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M8.56 2.75c4.37 6.03 6.02 9.42 8.03 17.72m2.54-15.38c-3.72 4.35-8.94 5.66-16.88 5.85m19.5 1.9c-3.5-.93-6.63-.82-8.94 0-2.58.92-5.01 2.86-7.44 6.32"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>360 feedback as conversation</h3>
          <p>Structured 360 feedback that feels like a real conversation, not a form. Richer responses. Better signal. No checkbox fatigue.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ip-card">
          <div class="ip-card-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M21 15a2 2 0 01-2 2H7l-4 4V5a2 2 0 012-2h14a2 2 0 012 2z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Skip-level &amp; employee listening</h3>
          <p>Skip-level interviews at scale — every manager's team heard from, not just the ones who speak up in all-hands. Quarterly listening programs with longitudinal tracking.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ip-card">
          <div class="ip-card-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3>HR investigation documentation</h3>
          <p>Structured documentation for HR investigations — consistent questions, complete records, chain of custody. Built for the legal and compliance requirements of formal HR processes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="ip-section">
    <div class="ip-section-inner">
      <p class="ip-section-label">The Data Problem, Solved</p>
      <h2>Patterns you couldn't see <em>when n=12.</em></h2>
      <div class="ip-card-grid">
        <div class="ip-card">
          <div class="ip-card-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><line x1="18" y1="20" x2="18" y2="10"/><line x1="12" y1="20" x2="12" y2="4"/><line x1="6" y1="20" x2="6" y2="16"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Retention signal, not noise</h3>
          <p>When 40% of departing employees mention the same manager in their exit interview, the data becomes undeniable. AnyInterview surfaces those patterns automatically.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ip-card">
          <div class="ip-card-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><polyline points="22 12 18 12 15 21 9 3 6 12 2 12"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Longitudinal listening</h3>
          <p>Run the same employee listening template quarterly. Watch how sentiment shifts before it shows up in attrition numbers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ip-card">
          <div class="ip-card-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 00-4-4H5a4 4 0 00-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 00-3-3.87M16 3.13a4 4 0 010 7.75"/></svg></div>
          <h3>Segment by team and tenure</h3>
          <p>Compare exit interview themes across departments, tenure bands, and performance quartiles. The insights that actually inform HR strategy.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="ip-closing">
    <div class="ip-closing-inner">
      <h2>Start hearing what your people <em>actually think.</em></h2>
      <p>Set up your first exit interview template in 90 seconds. Send it to every departing employee this quarter.</p>
      <a href="#" class="ip-cta-primary" data-action="open-demo">Book a Demo →</a>
      <p class="ip-closing-meta">Free to try <span class="dot"></span> No credit card <span class="dot"></span> Works for teams of 10 or 10,000</p>
    </div>
  </section>

</InnerLayout>

<style>
  .hr-cols { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 40px; margin-top: 8px; }
  .hr-cols p { font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--ink-soft); }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .hr-cols { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
</style>
